			"text": "ROOT",
			"relation": "null"
		},
		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 7,
			"text": "Acute promyelocytic leukemia ( APL ) is associated with reciprocal chromosomal translocations",
			"relation": "BACKGROUND"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "involving the retinoic acid receptor alpha ( RARalpha ) locus on chromosome 17 . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "In the majority of cases , RARalpha translocates and fuses with the promyelocytic leukemia ( PML ) gene",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "located on chromosome 15 . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "The resulting fusion genes encode the two structurally unique PML/RARalpha and RARalpha/PML fusion proteins as well as aberrant PML gene products ,",
			"relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "the respective pathogenetic roles of which have not been elucidated . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "We have generated transgenic mice",
			"relation": "ROOT"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 7,
			"text": "in which the PML/RARalpha fusion protein is specifically expressed in the myeloid-promyelocytic lineage . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 7,
			"text": "During their first year of life , all the PML/RARalpha transgenic mice have an abnormal hematopoiesis",
			"relation": "FINDINGS"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "that can best be described as a myeloproliferative disorder . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "Between 12 and 14 months of age , 10 % of them develop a form of acute leukemia with a differentiation block at the promyelocytic stage",
			"relation": "ADDITION"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 11,
			"text": "that closely mimics human APL even in its response to retinoic acid . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 13,
			"parent": 7,
			"text": "Our results are conclusive in vivo evidence",
			"relation": "FINDINGS"
		},
		{
			"id": 14,
			"parent": 13,
			"text": "that PML/RARalpha plays a crucial role in the pathogenesis of APL . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		}
	]
}